You know the stuff about how warrior fun we relatively lose to other classes : Criticals, taunting ability... At this moment there is nothing, except berserker frenzy and our &quot;3 expansion ago&quot; disciplines, that make a warrior fun to play. The only &quot;new&quot; thing a warrior can do is now some luclin AA abilities, like Area taunt, Rampage, Flurry, Warcry. Althought all those things are just useless (Bandages... Warcry...) or used in another purpose than intended (Area taunt is more used as a fix ta Taunt than a area thing).<br>
<br>
So what do you think of a new candy eye, Warrior only, situationnally usefull, like : <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">See the hate list</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> ! Let's call it the &quot;Warrior Insight&quot;. <br>
When you'll use it, you can see the 6 people lower than you in the list, assuming you're at the top. If you're not at the top of the list, you'll see the 3 above you and the 3 under you. For exemple :<br>
- You're tanking. you hit your Insight button, you can see a list (same as tracking list) with :<br>
    You<br>
    Clericdude<br>
    Pallydude<br>
    Othercleric<br>
    Rangertrueshot<br>
    ....<br>
- Now you're not tanking, you hit Insight : You see the 3 people above and the 3 below. If you're 2nd you see the one above and 5 below.<br>
<br>
I think it should be cool to get it at 51 (when you ding 51 you gain... nothing). With maybe some AA at 61+ for &quot;Warlord Insight&quot; (Increase the number of people you can see) or &quot;Sense of battle&quot; (Alow you to see if people on the list are gaining, loosing or keeping the same aggro generation).<br>
<br>
<br>
Of course, it doesn't help with the aggro issues we may have with Taunt. But it should be fun to have and I think it's not unbalancing, as long as we will not be able to see all the list, and to see the top of this list we must do our job anyway. <br>
What do you think ? Feel free to flame, to expose how it may be exploited and how get it may be unbalancing. I think it may be great, because we dont take the ability/role of any other class with, and it's in line with our class definition. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dobbofutreet@thesteelwarrior>Dobbo Futreet</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 791<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/03 3:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2056.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://images.flamingtext.com/clipart/icons/gen/War/Swords/Sword7.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Got an idea for a new warrior ability </span><hr size=1> I've had two (i like yours but)<br>
